\n| registration_plate = [[Vehicle registration plates of Austria|GB]]\n| postal_code_type   = [[List of postal codes in Austria|Postal code]]\n| postal_code        = 8967\n| area_code_type = [[Telephone numbers in Austria|Area code]]\n| area_code      = 03686\n| website   = [http://www.haus.at haus.at]\n| footnotes = \n}}\n'''Haus im Ennstal''' is a village in central [[Austria]], located in the [[Liezen (district)|Liezen district]] of [[Styria]]. It is an important town on the [[Enns (river)|Enns river]].\n\nHaus is a well-known [[ski resort]] and has hosted [[FIS Alpine Ski World Cup|World Cup]] [[Alpine skiing|alpine]] races several times, and the women's events of the [[FIS Alpine World Ski Championships|World Championships]] in [[FIS Alpine World Ski Championships 1982|1982]]. It offers a skiable field of {{convert|115|km|abbr=on}} served by 52 ski lifts.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|http://www.haus.at/}}\n\n{{Liezen}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Schladming Tauern]]\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Liezen District]]\n\n\n{{Styria-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n| name            = Haus im Ennstal\n| native_name     = \n| settlement_type = \n<!-- Images     -->\n| image_skyline   = \n| imagesize       = \n| image_caption   = \n| image_shield    = AUT Haus COA.jpg\n| shield_size     = 80x110px\n| shield_link     = \n<!-- Maps           -->\n| pushpin_map         = Austria\n| pushpin_mapsize     = 270\n| pushpin_map_caption = Location within Austria\n| image_map           = \n| mapsize             = \n| map_alt             =\n| map_caption         = Location within Liezen district\n<!-- Location    -->\n| coordinates       = {{coord|47|24|27|N|13|46|01|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type  = Country\n| subdivision_name  = [[Austria]]\n| subdivision_type1 = [[States of Austria|State]]\n| subdivision_name1 = [[Styria]]\n| subdivision_type2 = [[District (Austria)|District]]\n| subdiv